@node main "CYCAS DEMO - Help - Edit"
@toc "help.guide/main"


  Selecting and editing drawing elements:

  You edit elements by simply selecting the  elements  you
  want  to  work  on. To select the elements, the "Select"
  menu options will appear below the main menu instead  of
  any function list. The selection menu  enables access to
  all drawing elements. Its easier to use than explain!
 

  For example .. you want to delete a line you have drawn
  1) Select "Edit"
  2) Select "Delete" from the function list
  3) Use the mouse and click on the line you want to delete
  4) Select "OK"


  The  function  list  "Edit" contains edit functions like
  Copy or Move, etc.

  Therefore, in order to edit elements  you  first  choose
  the  elements you want to work on. All selected (active)
  elements are displayed white. If you leave the selection
  menu  using  the  button "OK", the function list reverts
  back and you continue.

  In the selection menu you activate  and  deactivate  all
  elements  you  want  to work on until you leave the menu
  using OK or  Exit.  While  selecting  elements  you  can
  change  the detail enlargement in order to have a better
  view of your drawing.

  In "Edit" you should pay attention to the function  Move
  /  Point.  This  function  offers  many possibilities in
  order to edit single points of the  elements.  I.e.  you
  can  use  Move / Point  to edit the dimensions linked to
  elements or you can  edit  3D elements  working  in  the
  various projections.

@endnode
